### ONCE — The Mythology

Six original creation myths forming the complete cosmology of a fantasy world. Not worldbuilding notes. He has built a moral philosophy from scratch — answers to the questions every civilization must answer: What are we for? What is evil? What happens when we die? What do we owe each other? — and followed each answer to its consequences, including the ugly ones. Gender, death, value, labor, sex, slavery, suicide, ecology, governance. Every piece flows from the cosmology. It is load-bearing all the way down.

**The six hymns:**

| Hymn | Domain |
|------|--------|
| **MOTHER** | Origin of the cosmos |
| **BROTHER** | Origin of Good and Evil |
| **WAR** | Evolution of humans |
| **GATE** | Origin of society |
| **CHOSEN** | Origin of authority |
| **CREED** | Origin of law |

He feels modern religions and societies have failed to provide a sufficient "why" for anything — so he invented a society that has a why and is showing its pros and cons. The myths began as foundation for Only Us. They have grown into something larger than scaffolding. They are the brand's primary shareable content until the novel exists.

He is developing them in a year-long writing workshop called Analog, led by Ravi Gupta (host of the Lost Debate podcast, author of *Garbage Town*). He joined for free after reconnecting with Ravi in Costa Rica.

> *"It's just one story. The oldest... Light versus Dark."*
> — Opening quote (Rust Cohle) of the September 2025 birthday letter to inner circle

> *"What's in me pours from my ears and nose but has yet to come out."*
> — Birthday letter, September 2025

