### The Marathon Script

Co-written with Otis Blum (Jason Blum's half-brother). About the first marathon runner in ancient Athens. Currently out to directors through their manager, John Burnham.

Evan carried this project. He did roughly 85% of the writing, convinced Otis of the opportunities, navigated the relationship, pushed back on rushing it out before the holidays. He's genuinely proud of how the script turned out. An earlier pass attracted producers, but it was conditional on one of them playing a lead he was wrong for — Evan and Otis backed out.

The script went out January 2026. First passes cited Nolan's competing marathon project. The more important lesson: the script consumed September 2025 through mid-January 2026 — five months substantially devoted to someone else's vehicle. Going forward, he needs to be ruthless about how much time goes to projects where someone else holds the keys.

